 \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Serb got straight back on serve, fuelled by chants of \\\"Nole\\\" ringing out on Court Philippe-Chatrier.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"score\": 0.8868189166523378, \"rank\": 0.1207647286030512, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\"}, {\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe-Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serving at deuce in the next game, Djokovic received his second time violation of the night and was hit with a loss of first serve.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1647718588633464e-16, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He landed the serve but lost the point andapproached the umpire, getting booed by the crowd in response.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world No.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2 was then hit with a code violation for audible obscenity and debated it with the official again.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he eventually retreated to the baseline to continue play, he gifted Musetti the break with an unforced error.\", \"